The BEST bar in DC. We stumbled onto Jackie Lees when we moved to the neighborhood and I can’t believe I ever lived without it.  The food is great - BBQ and “vegan junk food” vibes, and the drink selection is top. Bartenders / owners / friends - you cannot beat them.  It’s the type of place I would go to alone just to hang out, or bring out of town friends to. Somehow, it also manages to be “parent friendly” where my boomer parents feel right at home, too.  Lots of familiar faces every time we go - so I know I’m not alone in my opinions.  Be nice. Tip well. Come back often.

Get ready to meet your new favorite bar! While attending their soft launch, I realized how special Jackie Lee's will become to this neighborhood. The owners combined the history of the bar with a new level of elegance. If I had to describe the food in a single word: Dyn-O-Mite! We had the ribs, brisket sandwich, chicken tenders, and the plate of bacon. I'm a huge fan of beer/shot combos...and Jackie's offers several options. I'm looking forward to trying the other dishes on the menu and spending several nights creating new memories.
